# Clarity + Angular patterns

This project uses **Angular** with **standalone components** and **Clarity Design System**. The Angular app lives under the `angular/` directory.

## Module and imports

- Use **standalone components** (`standalone: true`). Do not rely on NgModules for feature code.
- Import `ClarityModule` from `@clr/angular` in each component that uses Clarity templates:
  `imports: [ClarityModule, CommonModule, ...]`
- Use `CommonModule` (or `NgFor`, `NgIf` from `@angular/common`) for `*ngFor`, `*ngIf`, `date` pipe, etc.

## Layout

- Page-level layout uses Clarity layout: `main-container` → `header` → `content-container` → `content-area`.
- Keep `<router-outlet>` where the app shell defines it (e.g. after the main container or inside content-area depending on routing).
- Use Clarity utility classes (e.g. `btn`, `alert`, spacing) instead of one-off custom CSS when possible.

## Forms

- Prefer **reactive forms** (`FormGroup`, `FormControl`) with Clarity form components.
- Use Clarity form containers (e.g. `clr-input-container`, `clr-select-container`) and directives (`clrInput`, `clrSelect`) so labels and validation display correctly.
- Document any app-specific form validation or error message patterns in this rule or in a shared form doc.

## Naming and structure

- **Components:** Use kebab-case for selectors (e.g. `datagrid`, `user-list`). Place component files in a folder named like the feature (e.g. `datagrid/datagrid.component.ts`).
- **Pages vs presentational:** Prefer “page” for route-level components that use the main layout; use presentational components for reusable pieces (e.g. datagrid, cards) that receive `@Input()` and emit `@Output()`.

## Styles

- Rely on Clarity’s CSS (`@clr/ui`). Avoid overriding Clarity variables or classes unless the project already defines a pattern (e.g. in `angular/src/styles.css` or a shared theme file).
- Use Clarity design tokens / CSS variables when extending (e.g. colors, spacing) so the UI stays consistent.

## Reference

- Clarity: [clarity.design](https://clarity.design/)
